revision.text:
{{DISPLAYTITLE:Ceiling_LowerAndCrushDist}} {{Special|97|tag, speed, crush[, dist [, crushmode]]|Ceiling|LowerAndCrushDist}}
* ''tag'': Tag of affected sector * ''speed'': How quickly the ceiling moves * ''crush'': Amount of damage to apply * ''dist'': Distance above the floor at which the movement will stop * ''crushmode'': Sets the [[crushing mode]]
==Usage==
Lowers the ceiling of affected sectors and applies crushing damage to anything under it. If ''tag'' is 0, then the sector on the line's back side is used.
This does not lower like other crushing ceilings. The actual height of the ceiling is changing. It will lower until it is ''dist'' units off the ground.
==Examples== {{noexamples}}
